    <brief sctype="array">
      <brief sctype="string">Configuration Management (ICM) enables you to track all types of data processing inventory by CPU, terminals, lines, software, personal computers, etc. In addition, it enables you to identify several types of configurations.</brief>
    </brief>
    <detail sctype="array">
      <detail sctype="string">Configuration Management (ICM) recognizes that each type of configuration item requires the storage of different information. Service Manager provides for this by grouping types of configuration items together. You may tailor individual tables and add additional tables to meet your facility's needs.</detail>
      <detail sctype="string"/>
      <detail sctype="string">The ICM provides you with the following tables to track information about basic types of configuration items.</detail>
      <detail sctype="string">- application</detail>
      <detail sctype="string">- computer</detail>
      <detail sctype="string">- displaydevice</detail>
      <detail sctype="string">- furnishings</detail>
      <detail sctype="string">- handhelds</detail>
      <detail sctype="string">- mainframe</detail>
      <detail sctype="string">- networkcomponents</detail>
      <detail sctype="string">- officeelectronics</detail>
      <detail sctype="string">- softwarelicense</detail>
      <detail sctype="string">- storage</detail>
      <detail sctype="string">- telecom</detail>
      <detail sctype="string"/>
      <detail sctype="string">In addition to the individual device type tables, ICM maintains the following tables to store information common to the individual tables:</detail>
      <detail sctype="string">- vendor</detail>
      <detail sctype="string">- location</detail>
      <detail sctype="string">- model</detail>
    </detail>
